The full name of A2n is Anti-2019-ncov, which means "anti-COVID-19" .

The full text is 2,632 words and takes about 5 minutes to read

Wuhan "After 90" Internet entrepreneur Yang Huijie decided to dispel rumors is from the mother hoarding Banlangen began.

After the outbreak, there was a rumor on the Internet that drinking Banlangen and fumigating vinegar could prevent pneumonia. Although the National Health and Health Commission later dismissed the rumor, it always seemed to run faster, yang Huijie's mother has ordered a large number of Banlangen from the Internet, also sent a batch to Yang Huijie.

At the same time, the truly effective means of protection has not yet taken root. On Jan. 20, Yang Huijie was on a business trip to Wuhan high-speed Railway Station when he noticed that only about one-third of the people wearing masks were wearing them, and almost no one in the closed carriages wore masks. A little worried, he sent a friend circle, his old friend in the Huazhong University of Science and Technology, Shanghai floating Ui designer l gave him a thumbs up.

The two became the founders of A2n, an online rumor-dispelling team. Yang Huijie told the Beijing News that the full name of A2n is Anti-2019-ncov, which means "fight against COVID-19" . With more and more people joining, A2n's work of "refuting rumors" is more and more extensive, including compiling popular science articles, translating Foreign Epidemic Literature, medical equipment information, consulting hospitals, manufacturers and so on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Internet rumor-dispelling team A2N volunteers are building a website. Photo courtesy of the respondents

━━━━━

The first document to dispel rumors has been read over a million times

Like Yang Huijie, l, who returned home on leave, was disturbed by all kinds of rumors. On the morning of January 22, she asked Yang Huijie, "have you seen any public accounts to dispel rumors? Rumors are flying everywhere, really can't stand it. " Yang Huijie replied, "No. " L said, "let's open one, I'll open it. " Yang Huijie replied, "ok, please pull. "

Fifteen minutes later, L set up a wechat group called "rumor crushing machine" and posted a group Qr Code in her friends' circle. She wrote down the group's Tenet: "Don't spread panic, collect rumors, crush rumors and keep up with the latest information. "

The first thing they did was to sort out a document on popular science and refuting rumors, which was divided into several sections, such as epidemic prevention measures and common sense, summary of official epidemic situation reports and policies, popular science of common errors, special area for refuting rumors, etc. , links to the actual source of each message are attached, and "rumors" are highlighted in red on the rumor-mongering images to prevent further spreading. Yang put the document on a graphite document for open editing, so that "everyone can see the real-time changes of the document and can also participate in updating and editing. "

"Rumor crusher" Wechat group and this 4273-word document, is the prototype of A2n. Most of the people who joined the group at first were alumni of Huazhong University of Science and Technology, but within two days, the number of people who joined the group began to explode. One group divided into five groups, and the group quickly expanded to 1,000 members. At the same time, 1.05 million people read the document to dispel rumors. This thoroughly exceeded the expectations of Yang Huijie, "in fact, a lot of people need to dispel rumors. "

In addition to regular readers who want to keep up with rumors, there are also international students who want to become volunteers, professionals with medical and biological backgrounds, doctors and nurses on the front lines, and government workers. A nurse in Chongqing specializes in writing popular science articles on "how to protect breastfeeding mothers and babies" during the epidemic, and several young programmers from Shandong Province hope to provide technical support for the subsequent development of A2n.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Within the rumor crusher group, the volunteers are having a discussion. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Clear Process and division of Labor

On the evening of January 23, Fire Lee, product manager of the post-1990s generation at an Internet company in Shenzhen, joined the "three groups" . The name is like the man, fire fire work wind fire, fierce and resolute.

After entering the "three groups, " she was stunned by what she saw. "rumors kept coming in, and 200 or 300 people in the group were talking about it, but no one was organizing it. It was chaotic. " As a product manager, fire is accustomed to meeting needs and solving problems, so she calls on the group to "write down your problems and then organize to see what to do next. "

Late that night, the fire with the quick-tempered Yang Huijie discuss, their first to organize the "three groups. ". She brought in the three most active members of the group as coordinators and assigned tasks based on their professional attributes and areas of expertise. A boy who works in human resources in a real estate company is responsible for setting up the organizational structure of the group. A girl who works carefully is responsible for researching the professional background of the volunteers in the group and the job they are looking forward to undertaking Another female student is in charge of planning the sections involved in refuting rumors. "It's like asking them to make some initial assumptions about the structure, the people, the content. "

The next day was the 30th day of the Lunar New Year. Early in the morning, Huo Huo and the three coordinators gathered in the group for a small meeting. The outcome of the meeting was that the content of the rumor was clarified, it mainly aims at the five aspects of the popularization of science, refuting rumors, donation information, document translation, and real-time epidemic situation of NCP, and clarifies the flow of information release, which is divided into three steps of rumor collection, Verification and release, and assign specific people to each of them.

The results of the discussions in the three groups were quickly used for reference by other groups. Several group leaders decided to identify the five major pieces of information from the three groups as five content groups, and each group chose its own content focus, at the same time, a separate volunteer co-ordination Group, Research Group, Publishing Group for the content group to provide services. The members of each group have a clear schedule, each on duty for one to two hours, both to ensure that key information is not missed, and not to add too much to the holiday burden.

Shortly after 11 p.m. on February 2, a reporter from the Beijing News noticed that the group leader was still leading the group members in their efforts to dispel rumors. If a suspected rumor is sent to the group, someone will be immediately@, the latter will quickly connect and verify, sending links to the group that can verify or disprove the information, and other members with resources will help verify it, everything is going in an orderly fashion.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A2N's disinformation public number.

Optimizing the norm of refuting rumors

Through a few days of fumbling, refueling small team in constant optimization refueling rumor norms. The fire told the Beijing News reporter, "The first priority is to get in touch with the person and make a phone call; if not, go to the state media and trust government websites and official media such as the People's Daily and CCTV; and the third is to see information issued by some authoritative opinion leaders, and we have to be clear about the sources at every step. "

On the evening of January 29, a video circulated among wechat friends of a man who claimed to have intercepted a batch of N95 masks for sale at the SF express outlet. One of fire fire's friends happened to work in the local Shunfeng company, she asked a friend, learned that there is no such thing, is the man in the video self-directed self-acting. The next day, the Panlong Public Security Bureau also issued a police report, saying that the man saw a mask placed in the business hall during the Mail, fabricated false video upload, has been punished.

On Jan. 31, rumors spread online that Wuhan No. 8 People's Hospital had expanded a large number of beds to allow patients who could not find a bed to pass through as soon as possible. One of the volunteers of the rumor-dispelling team happened to know the person in charge. He called to confirm that the rumor was false. The other party said that the rumor should be dispelled immediately, "otherwise the eight hospitals will be paralyzed. "

After obtaining the information, the document group volunteers will enter it into the document, which will then be synced by the volunteers of the publishing group on platforms such as Weibo and wechat public accounts. February 1, the website "A2n real-time epidemic platform" launched, their distribution channels are more diverse.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"A2n real-time Epidemic Platform" home.

A media friend told them to be wary of a "time-sensitive" rumour. The epidemic is changing rapidly, and some policies are rumored one day and rumored the next. "For this kind of information, we should mark the date when refuting rumors, otherwise after that time, refuting rumors become rumors, " Huo Huo said.

Not all rumors can be "refuted. ". As of 24:00 on February 1,274 pieces of information had been collected routinely, and 33 new ones had been added on that day, according to an internal daily, a rumor-dispelling team obtained by a reporter from the HSINKING newspaper, "The fire fire revealed that under normal circumstances, refutes the rumor rate is about 60% .

At present, the rumor-dispelling team is trying to expand the scope of dissemination, "even if I have one million views of a document, but this one million may only be young people, the elderly, people in remote areas, their cognition is still not enough, " said Yang Huijie.

Wang Jingyi, editor, Hsinking Daily News, proofread, Li Lijun
